            <title>[MAHOUT-141] Cluster Centroid improperly reported when no points associated w/ the cluster</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-141</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Per the discussion at &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.lucidimagination.com/search/document/5d54bb4822354bee/kmeans_help#48571ce2f5014a1f&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.lucidimagination.com/search/document/5d54bb4822354bee/kmeans_help#48571ce2f5014a1f&lt;/a&gt;, the Cluster class returns pointTotal as the centroid (center) of a Cluster with zero points, which is not correct.  It should return the Center as the centroid in this case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
